             British American Tobacco Plcâ€™s
Kenyan unit posted a 19 percent increase in half-year profit on
higher sales.  
 Net income in the six months through June rose to 1.02
billion shillings from 858 million shillings a year earlier, the
company said in a statement in the Daily Nation newspaper. Sales
climbed to 10.9 billion shillings from 9.02 billion shillings a
year earlier, it said.   
